===List of best-selling albums by foreign acts===
Aside from the Japanese-language materials recorded by either domestic or East Asian acts, at least forty out of all of the charting albums by foreign acts have sold more than one million copies in Japan. The following list covers the top-selling albums released by non-Japanese acts, including [[soundtrack album]]s, based on data provided by Oricon.<ref name="Japanese million albums"/> This data in many cases is incomplete, not accounting for import sales, re-issues or multiple versions of an album.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://chartmasters.org/2016/07/understanding-japanese-album-sales/9/|title=Understanding: Japanese Album Sales: III) Concrete Examples|last=Vieira|first=Guillaume|quote=If we consider all Oricon limits together, we can theoretically create a case of albums selling a million units within’ a few years without ever charting. With 4-5 different versions selling on various formats during high period of sales and with large imports can mean 20,000 copies sold a week in spite of being off the radar.|date=July 15, 2016|accessdate=January 9, 2018|publisher=Chart Masters}}</ref>

